<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1367,1969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1367,1392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Surstylus broadened and short (
<figureCitation box="[661,794,1367,1392]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[175,1403,235,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624696/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 5A, B</figureCitation>
); aedeagus nearly round apically (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1300,1367,1392]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[175,1403,235,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624696/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); gonopods semicircular and broadened laterally in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[764,853,1404,1429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[175,1403,235,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624696/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). The minimum interspecific genetic distance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pililobosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">S. pililobosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 8.3%, which is smaller than to other species (
<tableCitation box="[802,890,1439,1464]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="23.[147,225,546,566]" captionText="TABLE 2. Genetic distances within and between the 130 mtCOI sequences of 38 species of the coleoptrata, ornatipes, and undulata groups involved in the molecular analysis." pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="89" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1367,1969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1476,1501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Description.</emphasis>
Male: Frons brown, with 1 black band below. First flagellomere yellow, black at apical margin. Clypeus and palpus yellow. Mesonotum brownish to brown, with 3 pairs of yellow longitudinal stripes sublaterally (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,1548,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; Bâ€“J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Katepisternum white (
<figureCitation box="[515,602,1548,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; Bâ€“J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Scutellum brown (
<figureCitation box="[829,916,1548,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; Bâ€“J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Femur of foreleg with 3 long erect setae near distal part of posteroventral surface. Abdominal tergites dark brown medially, brownish laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1357,1583,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; Bâ€“J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[281,351,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[175,1403,235,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624696/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): Epandrium protruded ventrally, with ca. 28 setae on posterior portion per side. Surstylus with several setulae distally. Cercus lacking pubescence. Paramere with 2 setulae. Tenth sternite inverted triangular per side.
</paragraph>
